## Task 5 UDP and TCP

UDP:
- Connectionless, no delivery confirmation.
- Uses port numbers (1–65535).
- Analogy: standard mail without confirmation.
- Advantage: speed.
TCP:
- Connection-oriented, reliable delivery.
- User sequence numbers and acknowledgements.
- Three-way handshake: SYN → SYN-ACK → ACK.
- Uses port numbers (1–65535).

