## Task 6 Encapsulation

Each layer adds header/trailer:
- Application → Transport (segment/datagram).
- Transport → Network (IP packet).
- Network → Data Link (frame).
- Reverse process extracts data.
Life of a Packet:
- Browser sends HTTP request via HTTPS.
- TCP establishes connection.
- IP adds source/destination addresses.
- Link layer sends to router.
- Routers forward until destination.
- Reverse process at server.

